docs/ARM_CONTROL_API.md:3:`arm_control_bridge` is the high-level joint command gate for the simplified
docs/ARM_CONTROL_API.md:4:UAV arm. External modules should publish desired joint targets to `/arm/*`
docs/ARM_CONTROL_API.md:17:| `/arm/target_joints` | subscribe | `aerial_manip_msgs/msg/ArmCommand` | Validated high-level joint target input. |
docs/ARM_CONTROL_API.md:18:| `/arm/current_joint_state` | publish | `aerial_manip_msgs/msg/ArmState` | Current joint state normalized to configured joint order. |
docs/ARM_CONTROL_API.md:19:| `/arm/current_target` | publish | `aerial_manip_msgs/msg/ArmState` | Last accepted safe joint target. |
docs/ARM_CONTROL_API.md:34:`/arm/target_joints.command_mode` supports:
docs/ARM_CONTROL_API.md:36:- `joint_position`: use `joint_positions` as the new target.
docs/ARM_CONTROL_API.md:38:- `stow`: move to the configured `stow_joint_positions`.
docs/ARM_CONTROL_API.md:40:If `joint_names` is empty, joint arrays are interpreted in configured
docs/ARM_CONTROL_API.md:41:`joint_names` order. If `joint_names` is set, it must match the configured
docs/ARM_CONTROL_API.md:42:joint set; the bridge reorders values before publishing status and controller
docs/ARM_CONTROL_API.md:49:| `joint_names` | `["joint1", "joint2", "joint3"]` | Controlled joint names and canonical order. |
docs/ARM_CONTROL_API.md:50:| `initial_joint_positions` | `[0.0, 0.0, 0.0]` | Safe target used on startup. |
docs/ARM_CONTROL_API.md:51:| `stow_joint_positions` | `[0.0, 0.0, 0.0]` | Target used for `stow` commands. |
docs/ARM_CONTROL_API.md:52:| `min_joint_positions` | `[-1.57, -1.57, -1.57]` | Per-joint lower position limits in radians. |
docs/ARM_CONTROL_API.md:53:| `max_joint_positions` | `[1.57, 1.57, 1.57]` | Per-joint upper position limits in radians. |
docs/ARM_CONTROL_API.md:54:| `max_joint_velocities` | `[0.6, 0.6, 0.6]` | Per-joint velocity limits in radians per second. |
docs/ARM_CONTROL_API.md:55:| `target_jump_limit` | `0.35` | Maximum allowed per-command joint position jump in radians. |
docs/ARM_CONTROL_API.md:57:| `reach_tolerance` | `0.03` | Per-joint position tolerance for reached-target detection in radians. |
docs/ARM_CONTROL_API.md:61:The bridge rejects targets that contain non-finite values, violate joint
docs/ARM_CONTROL_API.md:63:`max_joint_velocities`, or use mismatched joint names.
